CELTIC striker John Guidetti has escaped punished after being found guilty of making ‘offensive’ comments in a Dutch interview.The Swede came to the attention of the SFA’s compliance officer Tony McGlennan in March when he was asked by show FC Rijnmond to sing a song that Hoops support chant about him at games.Reciting the lyrics, he said: &quot;Oh John Guidetti, puts the ball in the net-y, he’s a Super Swede and the h*** are deid, walking in Guidetti wonderland.&quot;Guidetti had contested the charge against him however in a Hampden hearing earlier today a disciplinary panel found him guilty of the offence.Despite the outcome, no further action will be taken against the 22-year-old.An SFA statement said: “The player was found in breach and censured.”